# RESTup v1.3

Lightweight pure JavaSE/6 HTTP server provides a RESTful API to the console applications 
(hereinafter - services). 
Interaction with the server is performed according to the following general scheme:
- get a list of services (GET), to determine the URI of the service;
- create a job to selected service (POST), to get the URI for the input files;
- send file(s) for the job (PUT);
- execute parameterized job (POST), to get the URI of the result files;
- get a list of result files (GET);
- get result file(s) (GET);
- delete the job and associated files (DELETE).

Server has an experimental WebDAV-based UI. An interface is a set of remote folders associated
with corresponding services. The service folder contains subfolders for input and output files.
UI can be accesed via WebDAV clients: Windows Explorer, Gnome Nautilus etc.

Project include java, PL/SQL (Oracle-XE compatible) agents (APIs) and freeware-based config 
examples (Linux/Windows). 
Examples require installed LibreOffice (4.x for Windows platform script) & Tesseract OCR. 

Contents:

/RESTup_server_v1.3_xxxx-EN.MD   ; documentation
/RESTupServer.jar                ; server 
/ServerStart.bat                 ; starting script for Windows
/ServerStart.sh                  ; starting script for Linux
/Linux/                          ; Linux config & examples                           
/Linux/RESTupConfig.xml          ; server config
/Linux/Echo.sh                   ; echo service script
/Linux/Office2x.sh               ; transform office docs service script
/Linux/Tesseract-OCR.sh          ; OCR service script
/Windows/                        ; Windows config & examples
/Windows/RESTupConfig.xml
/Windows/Office2x.js 
/Windows/Tesseract-OCR.js
/Agents/Oracle/restup_agent_package.sql ; PL/SQL RESTup agent package for Oracle
/Agents/Oracle/restup_agent_test.sql    ; PL/SQL package test script
/Agents/Java/                    ; self documented (javadoc) sources of
                                 ; the package org.net.restupAgent,
                                 ; package test, simple client, build scripts  
/Source/RESTupServer.java        ; server source
/Source/build.bat                ; build script
/Source/build.sh                 ; build script
/Source/Help.txt                 ; help template for WebDAV users

